Based on the results provided by protein-BLAST (provided below), the genes appear to code for a type III secretary protein SpaO, type III secretary protein SpaS, ATP synthase SpaL, antigen presentation protein SpaN, and/or type III secretary protein SpaR in Salmonella enterica. Since all of these proteins are all part of the surface presentation of antigens (Spa) group, they are involved in exporting antigens from the cell.
